post_text:
Congratulations to the Heritage Hills High School Academic Super Bowl team, a 2018 State Finalist! Good Luck May 5th at Purdue University! We hope that you will come to Purdue to support our team! The schedule for the day is:
10:15 a.m. Opening ceremonies
10:30 a.m. Fine Arts round
11:30 a.m. Social Studies round
12:30 p.m. Math round
1:30 p.m. English round
2:30 p.m. Science round
3:30 p.m. Interdisciplinary round
(awards will be presented at the end of each round)

For more information about State Finals, visit www.iasp.org/iace2/SuperStateFinals.html.
www.iasp.org/images/CongratulationsStateFinalist/HeritageHills.jpg

post_text: Join us for the Ford Drive 4 UR School event scheduled on March 17th from 9:00 AM to 2:00 PM on the Heritage Hills High School Campus. Each test drive generates $20 to the NS Athletic Department. This is not a sales event. No one from the dealership will be there for the purpose of selling vehicles, only to help generate money for our athletic department. Be there for the live remote with WITZ from 10:00 to 11:00. Make sure to bring a valid driver's license so you can test drive the latest in Ford.

post_text:
Heritage Hills High School Choral Department presents
Fright Night 2016: Toybox of Terror.
The toy room characters will be coming alive this week at Heritage Hills High School Auditorium. Come join them as they sing and dance to today's hits and classic oldies, with a spooky twist of course! Good for kids of all ages! You are sure to have a haunting good time and will be dancing in your seats. There will be a Trick-or-Treat trail following each performance.
Thursday, October 27 at 6:30 PM
Friday, October 28 at 6:30 PM (SPIRIT NIGHT)
Saturday, October 29 at 6:30 PM
Tickets go on sale at 4:45 PM. Doors open at 6:00 PM.
$5.00 adult
$3.00 student
5 and under are FREE
Receive $1.00 off if you wear a costume.
Hope to scare you there!

post_text:
The North Spencer School Corporation is seeking to connect the alumni and friends of Heritage Hills, Chrisney, Dale, and Gentryville high schools. The need for an Association like this is long overdue, and we recognize that the history of the community predates that of Heritage Hills. Our goal in forming this organization is to:

§ facilitate alumni gatherings

§ honor/recognize individuals who have come from our schools

§ better connect to and enrich the community through the school system that serves our area

To enrich this feeling of pride for our schools we have named the organization the Spirit of North Spencer. We hope to spread feelings of support for our school system and honor to the schools that once served our area. We would greatly appreciate your assistance in making this organization successful and continuing the tradition of spirit for our schools.

Please check it out on Facebook. Spirit of North Spencer

https://www.facebook.com/groups/1711145965803423/

post_text:
***ATTENTION FOOTBALL PARENTS & PLAYERS***



Former Patriots, Jon Goldsberry, Seth Johannemann, Alex Bettag and several former teammates of Jon Goldsberry that played Division 1 and/or Professional Football have joined him to kick off the First Annual Southern Indiana Football and Life Skills Youth Summer Camp. The camp will be for Grades 7-12 (entering 2013 season) and will be held at Heritage Hills High School on June 21-22.

Football players in the Tri-State area deserve an opportunity to meet and learn from a group of guys that have had the opportunity to experience something many kids dream of, but few actually get the chance to do.

This camp won't apply to all of you, but I graciously ask for your support by clicking the "Share" button below, regardless of where you are on the map. Jon, Seth and Alex would really appreciate your support and they look forward to a great camp in June!



Registration will end on June 19th so please visit www.JonGoldsberry.com to register or for more information you can contact Jon Goldsberry at camp@jongoldsberry.com.

post_text: Great presentation by Technology Integration Committee at last night's Board meeting on the merits of issuing all students in grades 5-12 email addresses through Google Docs. This will open up the potential of this tool to enhance instruction and better prepare our learners for the 21st Century. More information will follow BEFORE the emails are activated.

post_text: North Spencer School Safety Specialists met with State Police today to discuss partnership that provides greater law enforcement presence in our schools. The plan is to provide work space and access within our school campuses. We are also reaching out to towns and county officers with the hope of establishing an even closer relationship with our outstanding law enforcement officers.
